text: San Juan County is a county in the U.S. state of New Mexico. As of the 2020 census, the population was 121,661, making it the fifth-most populous county in New Mexico. Its county seat is Aztec. The county was created in 1887. ==References== Category:New Mexico counties Category:1880s establishments in New Mexico Territory Category:1887 establishments in the United States
title: San Juan County, New Mexico
